# Berth configuration — copy to .env.local and edit. All vars are optional.

# Where to bind the dev/prod server (loopback by default — keep it on 127.0.0.1
# unless you're fronting it with `tailscale serve` or a reverse proxy you trust).
# BERTH_PORT=5202
# BERTH_HOST=127.0.0.1

# SQLite location. Defaults to ~/.berth/berth.db.
# BERTH_DB=/home/you/.berth/berth.db

# Markdown registry. Defaults to ~/PORTS.md. If neither exists, Berth starts
# with an empty registry and you add apps from the UI.
# BERTH_PORTS_MD=/home/you/PORTS.md

# Extra hostnames for Vite's `allowedHosts` (dev only). Comma-separated.
# Use a leading dot to match any subdomain. Loopback (localhost / 127.0.0.1)
# and `.ts.net` (any Tailscale tailnet) are always allowed by default —
# only add LAN hostnames, custom domains, or reverse-proxy fronts here.
# Example: BERTH_ALLOWED_HOSTS=berth.lan,.example.com
# BERTH_ALLOWED_HOSTS=
